original_title: Richmond: St. Pauls Avenue - Van Duzer Street
text:
St. Pauls Avenue, east side, south of Van Duzer Street, showing the Chapel of Our Lady of Consolation (R.C.) and the abandoned fire house of Engine 204, Tompkinsville.

original_title: Richmond: Van Duzer Street - St. Pauls Avenue
text:
561-563 Van Duzer Street, east side, at St. Pauls Avenue. This old brick house was owned by J. Oneill in 1874 and by Chas. Rosenberg from 1907 to 1917. Dates refer to maps on which the owners' names appear.

July 8, 1932

P. L. Sperr
